cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.CY

The paper deals with image steganography, which is a subfield of information security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category. The paper also involves image processing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of encryption and shuffling algorithms indicates that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a new technique for grayscale images, which could make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
